{"_id":"On2ZrPJTe8FURsXY","name":"Operative Exploit","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.classes.uf8ADOAeBrtUkPVl]{Operative}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">As you gain experience, you learn special tricks called operative exploits. You learn your first operative exploit at 2nd level, and you learn an additional exploit every 2 levels thereafter. If an operative exploit allows a saving throw to resist its effects, the DC is equal to 10 + half your operative level + your Dexterity modifier. If it requires an enemy to attempt a skill check, the DC is equal to 10 + 1-1/2 &times; your operative level + your Dexterity modifier. The list of operative exploits appears on page 95. You cannot learn the same exploit more than once unless it specially says otherwise.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>2nd Level</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.c84usvQez3sMyhmj]{Alien Archive (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.QJjE9tvp0YFNhjfg]{Armor Optimizer (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.uZa83E9JvgkMLtzW]{Combat Trick (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.wlrYsn05dMaEpe5K]{Field Treatment (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.ejMFotFoC7gbTqvh]{Holographic Clone (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.FdhfWip1bVpjOHOp]{Inoculation (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.eseniVOUmdIC9kAe]{Jack of All Trades (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.P6aQ6Wpt5KOZEjIF]{Nightvision (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.Z3MPGoaXFFLHxv35]{Quick Disguise (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.Suznr1WSCjd8lRMo]{Uncanny Mobility (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.NaGCVIyrwQsH8bV5]{Uncanny Pilot (Ex)}</p>\n<h2>6th Level</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.OAVc1W07QUCBNS94]{Bleeding Shot (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.rKRXkuuYb1KXP8wG]{Certainty (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Comp