{"_id":"Suznr1WSCjd8lRMo","name":"Uncanny Mobility (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.On2ZrPJTe8FURsXY]{Operative Exploit}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl19_LabelName\">When you make a trick attack, if you choose the target of your attack before you move, your movement doesn’t provoke attacks of opportunity from that target. When you use your standard action to move, you can choose one creature; you don’t provoke attacks of opportunity from that creature for this movement.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Operative Exploit","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"SvjHeYcqBNY1lcDH","name":"Reaction Insight (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.s2666UOaMcZCw251]{Reaction}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\"><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">You gain Improved Combat Maneuver (dirty trick) as a bonus feat and a +2 insight bonus to Physical Science checks.</span><br></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Reaction","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"Aspect Insight","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TBIzd27ZlnFp6eyS","name":"Technomantic Proficiency (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.sobLlAGQkmWcFBFx]{Magic Hack}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl18_LabelName\">As a standard action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to temporarily learn how to use a weapon in combat. Choose a single weapon; you gain proficiency with it (and any identical weapon) for a number of minutes equal to your class level. Each round you use the weapon reduces this magic hack’s duration by 1 minute. For example, at 4th level, you could gain proficiency with corona laser rifles for 4 minutes. If you fire such a weapon for 2 rounds, you remain proficient with it for 2 more minutes.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Technomancer","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"none","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"none","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TBMx5RtvuycSu9LP","name":"Momentum Embodiment (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.hxGhCeOFrN0keV9A]{Momentum}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">Once per combat, when you move a distance greater than your normal speed in one turn (using multiple move actions, the run full action, or a bonus to speed that allows you to move beyond your normal maximum), you can gain 1 Entropy Point without taking any additional action.<br></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Momentum","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"Aspect Embodiment","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TQ2bp29Gdbvhru6r","name":"Sustained Determination (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.hIhgdXnqGHBm0A64]{Envoy Improvisation}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl49_LabelName\">As a move action, you can spend 2 Resolve Points to grant an ally within 60 feet 1 Resolve Point that he can spend to empower one of his abilities, even if he has spent all of his own Resolve Points. The ally must spend the Resolve Point before the start of your next turn; if he does not do so, he loses the Resolve Point and you still lose the Resolve Points you spent. You can’t grant the same ally the benefits of this ability again until both you and your ally have recovered your Resolve Points after an 8-hour rest or its equivalent.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Improvisation","type":"","activation":{"type":"move","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"none","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"none","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"8th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TZ7Al2N1AAAWxTUj","name":"Alleviate Pain (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.kHeZbTmU7JXi8dbX]{Pharmacology}</p>\n<p>As a standard action, you can create and deliver a formula to a living creature to prevent pain and nausea. When injected, the mixture provides the target with a +4 enhancement bonus to saving throws against pain effects and effects that cause the sickened or nauseated condition. This bonus lasts for 1 minute. If the target is already under one of these effects, or if it already has the sickened or nauseated condition, it can immediately attempt a new saving throw with a +2 enhancement bonus to end the effect or remove the condition. This does not grant a new saving throw if the effect did not originally allow one. If you are at least 7th level, the bonus to saving throws against pain effects and effects that cause the sickened or nauseated condition increases to +6, or +4 for targets already afflicted and attempting a new saving throw. If you are at least 13th level, this automatically removes the sickened condition, and the bonus to new saving throws for the other conditions increases to +6.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Pharmacology","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"none","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"none","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"Breakthrough","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TguNcpqReCw2GpAZ","name":"Treatment Mastery (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.rpaon3jF3nCe5eP9]{Theorem (Ex)}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your Medicine check when using the treat disease and treat drugs or poison tasks, and can do so with greater speed. It takes you 1 minute to treat disease, and a move action to treat drugs or poison. You can also attempt these tasks without a medkit, medical lab, or medical bay, though doing so takes the normal amount of time for both tasks and you do not gain the bonus to the checks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Theorem","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TiZk92hHuM9XNWTZ","name":"Expert Attack (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.hIhgdXnqGHBm0A64]{Envoy Improvisation}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl42_LabelName\">As a move action, you can spend 2 Resolve Points to add your bonus from expertise to your next attack roll before the end of your turn.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Improvisation","type":"","activation":{"type":"move","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"none","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"none","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"8th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TpIFhqDUrNkdiEk0","name":"Uncanny Agility (Ex) (Operative)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.classes.uf8ADOAeBrtUkPVl]{Operative}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">You are immune to the flat-footed condition, and your opponent doesn’t gain any bonuses to attack rolls against you from flanking you or attacking you when you’re prone. Furthermore, covering fire and harrying fire don’t provide any advantage against you.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Operative","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"7th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TpQFUzCF5V1DbDdi","name":"Kill Shot (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.classes.cCZQpV0NmYE9qZoL]{Soldier}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">As a standard action, you can make a single attack against an enemy. If the attack hits and does not kill your enemy, you can expend 1 Resolve Point to force the creature to succeed at a Fortitude save or die. Once you&rsquo;ve used this ability on a creature (regardless of whether or not you forced it to attempt a Fortitude save), that creature is immune to your kill shot for 24 hours.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Soldier","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"none","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"none","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"20th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"TqoEKDXiRdDyBmp7","name":"Solar Acceleration (Su)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.UVNOjH2ERlQjcGnU]{Zenith Revelation}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl60_LabelName\">When you’re fully photon-attuned, you can make a full attack as a standard action. In addition, you and up to six allies within 30 feet are affected by <em>haste</em> (see page 358) for 1 minute after you use this revelation. At 17th level, the extra speed from the <em>haste</em> effect increases to 60 feet (to a maximum of three times the creature’s normal speed).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Solarian","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"none","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"none","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"Zenith Revelation","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/sfrpg/images/cup/gameplay/photon.png"}
{"_id":"UJx5Gk6p6SdlTcHl","name":"Extended Spell (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.sobLlAGQkmWcFBFx]{Magic Hack}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl27_LabelName\">When you cast a spell, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to double its duration. This has no effect on spells with a duration of concentration, instantaneous, 1 round or less, or permanent, nor can it increase a spell’s duration to more than 24 hours.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Technomancer","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"5th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"UKOpnFFzqflPY9c5","name":"Retrocognition (Sp)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.Hj7rGHmzQGP8rEGB]{Empath}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You can use @Compendium[sfrpg.spells.jgLKmk5n9QzQUCNq]{Retrocognition}&nbsp;as a spell-like ability at will. When doing so, you take a –2 penalty to saving throws against mind-affecting effects for as long as you concentrate on <em>retrocognition</em> and an equal amount of time afterward. You can spend 1 Resolve Point to negate this penalty.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Empathy Connection","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"15th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"UNxexURTq242nxj4","name":"Peer into the Future (Su)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.2N7K20WTe9aA7ivW]{Akashic}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">Once per day, you can spend 10 minutes in uninterrupted meditation to receive visions of possible futures. At any point over the next 24 hours, you can declare that you are using the benefit of this ability before rolling one initiative check, saving throw, or skill check. You gain a +4 insight bonus to that check. At 11th level, you can use this ability twice per day, though you can’t use it again until after you’ve used your first bonus.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Akashic Connection","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"6th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"UVNOjH2ERlQjcGnU","name":"Zenith Revelation","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.classes.kuEdVbzv5zXIO4wk]{Solarian}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">At 9th level and again at 17th level, you gain two powerful stellar revelations. Choose two revelations from the zenith revelations list: one graviton revelation and one photon revelation. The list of zenith revelations begins on page 107.<br><br>Zenith revelations are powerful stellar revelations that require you to be fully attuned in a stellar mode. After using a zenith revelation, your stellar mode immediately becomes unattuned.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Graviton Revelations</h2>\n<p><sub><img src=\"systems/sfrpg/images/cup/gameplay/graviton.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\"></sub> @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.NjLi4QFTp4ahZgy2]{Starquake (Su)}</p>\n<p><sub><img src=\"systems/sfrpg/images/cup/gameplay/graviton.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\"></sub> @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.2tlvfJ5a9H8LYpiQ]{Time Dilation (Su)}</p>\n<p><sub><img src=\"systems/sfrpg/images/cup/gameplay/graviton.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\"></sub> @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.IuY4xCmRlUwPZhZ2]{Wormholes (Su)}</p>\n<h2>Photon Revelations</h2>\n<p><sub><img src=\"systems/sfrpg/images/cup/gameplay/photon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\"></sub> @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.WqbHK6rJL7fWUVvF]{Miniature Star (Su)}</p>\n<p><sub><img src=\"systems/sfrpg/images/cup/gameplay/photon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\"></sub> @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.mf804jWpiONVC3Bt]{Ray of Light (Su)}</p>\n<p><sub><img src=\"systems/sfrpg/images/cup/gameplay/photon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\"></sub> @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.TqoEKDXiRdDyBmp7]{Solar Acceleration (Su)}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Solarian","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"9th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"UXeVNfhnnkWSRd3M","name":"Keen Observer (Ex; Sense Motive)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.DR8JvF0xiwsXggxj]{Expertise Talent}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl22_LabelName\">Whenever you interact with a creature under a mental effect for at least 1 minute, the GM attempts an automatic secret Sense Motive check for you without your expertise die. On a success, you learn about the mental effect. If you specifically request a Sense Motive check to sense mental effects, you can attempt a Sense Motive check as normal, including your expertise die, in addition to this automatic check.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Expertise Talent","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"UZMGMjpAwhGZNurI","name":"Coordinated Assault (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.classes.HNCQFSPw4DVTATHv]{Mechanic}</p>\n<p>If you have a drone, whenever both you and your drone make attacks against the same target, you each receive a +1 circumstance bonus to your attack rolls. If you have an exocortex instead, whenever you and your exocortex are both attempting to hack a system, you each receive a +1 circumstance bonus to the checks to gain access. In either case, these bonuses increase to +2 at 17th level.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Mechanic","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"11th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"UZjMSvXesViIrJl8","name":"Stealth Drone","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"chassis","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.Y4ajp13ACVnzaS5s]{Drone Chassis}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl02_LabelName\">Sleek and covered in a light-absorbing alloy, the stealth drone prowls along the ground on multiple small legs, silenced wheels, an air cushion, or some similar form of propulsion. This drone specializes in stealth and infiltration and can vanish almost entirely from sight as long as it remains perfectly still.</span></p>\n<h2>Initial Mods</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl02_LabelName\">@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.mZpIDgU1G1aHudu2]{Climbing Claws (Ex)}, @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.ZCNA7qg5Hz6Jirs0]{Reactive Camouflage (Ex)}, @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.dDZLj7L4psee7UZc]{Weapon Mount (Ex)}</span></p>\n<h2>Bonus Skill Unit</h2>\n<p>Stealth @Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.6cm9UHSlmWPU9QQe]{Skill Unit (Ex)}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","type":"","modifiers":[],"levels":1,"size":"small","speed":{"value":40,"special":"climb 20 ft."},"eac":10,"kac":12,"fort":"slow","ref":"fast","will":"slow","abilityScores":{"str":12,"dex":14,"con":"-","int":6,"wis":10,"cha":6},"abilityIncreaseStats":{"first":"dex","second":"wis"},"damage":{"parts":[]},"critical":{"parts":[]},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"V7UpT4PWsXmFN5x9","name":"Robot Influence (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.sobLlAGQkmWcFBFx]{Magic Hack}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl13_LabelName\">You can affect constructs, robots, and other creatures that have the technological subtype with your mind-affecting spells, even if they’re mindless or normally immune to such effects. However, they receive a +2 bonus to their Will saves against your mind-affecting spells.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Technomancer","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"VBUwdNhZStP54DTN","name":"Engineer's Eye (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.YMGOKoZtKgJqIsAD]{Mechanic Trick}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl27_LabelName\">When you are within 10 feet of a trapped or malfunctioning machine or computer, you receive a free Computers, Engineering, or Perception check (as decided by the GM) to notice the trap or defect, whether or not you are actively looking. In addition, due to your intimate knowledge of your ship, you receive one of these checks whenever you board your ship to notice if anything is wrong with the ship’s systems.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Mechanic","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"8th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"VDaL3dTtI6hpiyQf","name":"Gear Boost","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.classes.cCZQpV0NmYE9qZoL]{Soldier}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">At 3rd level and every 4 levels thereafter, you learn a trick called a gear boost that make you better with a particular type of weapon or armor. Choose from the gear boosts listed below. Some gear boosts require you to reach a certain soldier level to select them; this level is indicated in parentheses after the boost’s name.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.XjGuTb3vud4CeLQB]{Anchoring Arcana (Su; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.QQ5lHJOrIZpgcbBQ]{Armored Advantage (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.9OrlXfTxMDP4GKjW]{Brutal Blast (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.IjvpIo3oGJJRPw2s]{Bullet Barrage (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.1r0WJ0Adq0f1C78e]{Electric Arc (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.M9YzLGbJCL2fMlWl]{Flash Freeze (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.cBujK5UWCKmqam60]{Heavy Onslaught (Ex; 11th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.Olymbfyy5k2JY8hB]{Laser Accuracy (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.GoXXOPGD32mckcuD]{Melee Striker (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.p9r7NTZOUcw9ci81]{Plasma Immolation (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.zPeO9VWyAKI4LRII]{Powerful Explosive (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.0lPCh8embCwjt2ii]{Sonic Resonance (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Soldier","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"VQJ68qx5UIbzz8oK","name":"Situational Awareness (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.hIhgdXnqGHBm0A64]{Envoy Improvisation}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl48_LabelName\">If you ready an action, once before the trigger you selected occurs, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to change both the trigger and the action you have ready. You must ready an action that takes the same kind of action as your originally readied action, or you must ready a lesser action. (For example, if you readied a standard action, you could switch to another standard action, a move action, or a swift action, and if you readied a move action, you could switch to another move action or a swift action.)</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Improvisation","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"8th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"Vdup0NdLq6ZiLnml","name":"Flashing Strikes (Ex) (Vanguard)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.classes.WDvGdJ5mMpAD9cWQ]{Vanguard}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">Your mastery of melee combat allows you to make multiple attacks more accurately. When making a full attack entirely with melee attacks, you take a –3 penalty instead of the normal –4 penalty.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Vanguard","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"11th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"W2SaEwkr6GyxKNYs","name":"Blindsight (Su)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.Dysu4F8licjEb2FY]{Vanguard Discipline}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">Your ability to detect anomalous atomic vibration improves. You gain blindsight (heat) with a range of 20 feet. You must have selected the blindsense discipline or have blindsense (heat) from another source before you select this discipline.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Vanguard Dscipline","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"10th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"W8lD1ZYoRuibeos2","name":"Glean Spell (Su)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.class-features.2N7K20WTe9aA7ivW]{Akashic}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">Once per day, you can delve into the Akashic Record to cast a spell from either the mystic or technomancer spell list as if it were on your list of spells known. The spell consumes a spell slot 1 level higher than the level of the spell.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Akashic Connection","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"18th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"_id":"WHSxEq59wBSVTlVi","name":"Spells (Mystic)","permission":{"default":0,"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.classes.bItuvukGHbObTApr]{Mystic}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.kJBtVnrP6WjDRztl]{Mystic - Spells list}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">You cast spells drawn from the mystic spell list (see page 336). To learn or cast a spell, you must have a Wisdom score equal to at least 10 + the spell’s level. The Difficulty Class for a saving throw against your spell is 10 + the spell’s level + your Wisdom modifier.<br><br>You can cast only a certain number of spells of each spell level per day. Your number of spells per day is given on Table 4–4: Mystic. In addition, you receive bonus spells per day if you have a Wisdom modifier of +1 or higher, as shown on Table 4–5: Mystic Bonus Spells—note that you only receive these bonus spells once you can cast spells of that level normally. You can also cast 0-level spells. These spells are cast like any other spell, but there is no limit to how many 0-level spells you can cast each day.</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">Your selection of spells is limited. You begin play knowing four 0-level spells and two 1st-level spells of your choice. At each new mystic level, you learn one or more new spells, as indicated on Table 4–6: Mystic Spells Known. Unlike spells per day, the number of spells you know isn’t affected by your Wisdom modifier.<br><br>Every time you gain a level, you can swap out one spell you already know and learn a single new spell of the same level in its place. In effect, you lose the old spell in exchange for the new one. You must choose whether or not to swap the spell at the same time you gain new spells known for the level.<br><br>You can cast any mystic spell you know at any time, assuming you have not yet used up your allotment of spells per day for the spell’s level. You can also cast a spell using a higher-level spell slot. For instance, if you want to cast a 1st-level spell but have used up all your 1st-level spells for the day, you can use a spell from a 2nd-level slot instead if you have one.<br><br>You can also decipher magical inscriptions that would otherwise be unintelligible or, as a full action, identify any spells encoded in a spell gem as a full action. This does not normally invoke the magic contained within, although it may do so in the case of a cursed or trapped spell gem.</span></p>\n<h2>Spells Per Day</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\"></span></p>\n<table class=\"inner\" style=\"height: 336px; width: 205px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 57.2px; height: 16px;\"><strong>Level</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 20.4px; height: 16px;\"><strong>1st</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 22.8px; height: 16px;\"><strong>2nd</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\"><strong>3rd</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\"><strong>4th</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\"><strong>5th</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 20.4px; height: 16px;\"><strong>6th</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 57.2px; height: 16px;\">1st</td>\n<td style=\"width: 20.4px; height: 16px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 22.8px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 20.4px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 57.2px; height: 16px;\">2nd</td>\n<td style=\"width: 20.4px; height: 16px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 22.8px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 21.2px; height: 16px;\">-</td>\n<td style=\"wid